    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my blueberry bushes are turning kind of yellow on the leaves. i cant tell if they need more nitrogen or if the soil pH is just messed up. any idea how to tell the difference?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on blueberry bushes, or chlorosis, can indeed be caused by both nutrient deficiencies and soil pH issues. If the yellowing starts on the older, lower leaves, it might point toward nitrogen or other mobile nutrient deficiencies. Conversely, if the new growth is yellow while the veins remain green, it could strongly suggest a pH problem, as bluebirds are acid-lovers. You can test your soil's pH levels to get a definitive answer before adding fertilizer.",
      "source": "target",
