      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those tunnels and holes, even without many earthworms, could be signs of various soil-dwelling pests or fungal activity that is stressing your roots. Small root feeders, like certain types of nematodes or slugs, can create galleries that damage fine root hairs, leading to poor nutrient and water absorption. If the roots themselves look brown, mushy, or foul-smelling, that strongly suggests a pathogen, like root rot, is the primary culprit, not just a nutrient lack.",
